caption: Worst starbucks i have ever been to. I have no idea how any of them even got jobs, let alone got into a car to drive to work. I ordered, and i counted, 27 people that came in after me all got their order before me. The workers are so oblivious you can’t even ask them what the weather is. Can confidently say this is the worst customer service i have ever had in my life and i hope no one wastes their time here. ridiculous.

I try to be as mindful of other people as much as possible, especially the coffee shop workers around 8-9am when people are ordering left and right before they go to their offices. So I ordered my feta wrap and iced coconut milk latte via the SB app. I ordered it as I was getting on the Red Line at 07:48. The app said my order will be ready in 5-6 minutes. Cool, gives them more time in case they are super busy. I arrived there at 08:05 and my order is still not there. My coffee arrives at around 08:09 but my feta wrap is nowhere. So I asked someone and she asked the person in charge of the baked goods/sandwiches at the other end. That was the most horrendous, rude reply at your place of work I've ever heard. She said "I don't know." The person I asked, thankfully said, "she ordered it 20 minutes ago?!" but rude girl just replied "I don't know, someone probably took it." Then rolled her eyes. I guess  that was her manager but the person I asked promptly said "OK, please get one made now?" And rude girl shouted, as if she had the hardest job on the planet "It's coming, it's coming, it's coming!!!" I seriously can't believe all this happened 2 hours into their shift in the morning. I finally got out the door at 08:16, almost 30 minutes from when I ordered from my phone. I'll try to avoid this location from now on.

I waited a long time for 2 Chai Tea Lattes. When I got them, they tasted watered down after I asked that it not have water. I told the barista and he said he would be happy to remake them. Considering the long wait time, I asked for a refund. He let me keep the drinks. I went over to the manager to process the refund and she asked me to return the drinks. I told her that he barista had already said I could keep them, and you could tell she wasn't pleased. After processing the refund she told the barista he couldn't do that. I logged into my Starbucks app this morning only to see the credit was reversed!! Horrible service.
